author: @The_Crucible714
content: I can mark the milestones in my life by Madonna’s hits. Like the female Elvis (with 4 decades of staying power) little Miss “Louise Ciccone” has certainly made a name for herself. I remember one could always count on her - and Miss Grace Jones to be at least two hours late when they appeared in the NYC clubs back in the day, but of course it was totally worth it! I also love the fact that Lady M totally supports the LGBTQ+ community, not like some female artists >cough cough< Donna Summer who blamed her affiliation with gays as a “total lapse in judgement” when she was “under the influence” and fell from ”the anointed path.” Now, not being one to speak ill of the dead I can only say; ”Donna Summer’s dead? Good.” Madonna realizes who made her name a household word world-wide and her allegiance to the community has never faltered. In fact she’s had some of “The Dolls” from RPDR appear in her shows/on tour (ie; “Bob the Drag Queen,” etc.) How lucky you are to be at one of the most idyllic places on earth to view the most iconic female vocalist to date!
